AIDA Dataset Register

Information on datasets shared on the AIDA Data Hub.

The most important factor for building world-class AI is access to massive amounts of high-quality training data. We help researchers collaboratively gather, annotate, share and enrich large volumes of research data for machine learning in medical imaging diagnostics.

This register shows information on datasets that we have helped researchers share with the world, to make their high-quality datasets more FAIR and citeable using Digital Object Identifiers (DOI).

So far 2.36TB data have been shared, in 4462 scans with 0 annotations in 1 datasets, according to clinical data acquisition priorities

You can also Search, see Metrics, use the API, or learn more about FAIR and DOI.
